relevant_labels.prompt:
You are a helpful assistant that can generate relevant class names for the task description. You will be given a task description. Your goal is to generate {N} new class names relevant to the task, set in a real-world environment. The generated class names must: Be semantically or visually relevant to the task description. Represent plausible but distinct categories. Avoid duplicates or trivial variations (e.g., just adding numbers or “object”). Stay within the same domain or environment as described in the task description. 

Input: 
Task Description: {short description of the desired task} 
Number of class names to generate: {N} 
Output: A list of {N} new class names that are relevant classes pertaining to the task description. 

Example Input: 
Task Description = {“Arrange dishes and utensils on a dining surface.”} 
Number of class names: 6 
Output: Relevant classes = [“bowl”, “plate”, “table”, “fork”, “knife”, “napkin”].
